Custom Tags
1. When the inbuilt JSP tags are not enough for the business requirements, we can create 
   custom tags

2 Steps to creating custom tags
1. Create the Tag Handler Class
2. Map the custom tag handler class inside a file called Tag Lib Descriptor (tld) - 
   an .xml file that allows us to pass in some properties into the tag handler class at 
   runtime


4 Lifecycle Methods
1. setPageContext()
2. doStartTag()
3. doEndTag()
4. release()